# Python Port Plan: 00_config

Port the Ruby `Boukensha` configuration library from
`week1_baseline/ruby/00_config` to Python at `week1_baseline/python/00_config`.

## Goal

Reproduce the behaviour and public surface of the Ruby step 0 library in
idiomatic Python. A `Config` class loads settings from an external
`.boukensha/` directory, and stateless task classes resolve provider, model, and
system prompt per task. The example script must print the same information as the
Ruby example.

## Source inventory (Ruby)

| Ruby file | Role |
|-----------|------|
| `lib/boukensha.rb` | top level require aggregator |
| `lib/boukensha/config.rb` | `Boukensha::Config` (dir resolution, env load, settings load, MUD accessors, nested `dig`) |
| `lib/boukensha/tasks/base.rb` | abstract stateless `Tasks::Base` (provider, model, prompt resolution) |
| `lib/boukensha/tasks/player.rb` | concrete `Tasks::Player` (defines `task_name`) |
| `prompts/system.md` | default system prompt shipped with the library |
| `examples/example.rb` | runnable smoke test |
| `Gemfile` | declares the `dotenv` dependency |

